# Command s3cmd

## What does this command do:

S3cmd is a free command line tool and client for uploading, retrieving and managing data in Amazon S3 and other cloud storage service providers that use the S3 protocol, such as Google Cloud Storage or DreamHost DreamObjects. It is best suited for power users who are familiar with command line programs. It is also ideal for batch scripts and automated backup to S3, triggered from cron, etc.

## Installed from

For Fedora install using: sudo dnf install s3cmd
For Raspberry Pi install using: sudo apt install s3cmd
For Mac install using: brew install s3cmd

## Command path

For Fedora run: /usr/bin/s3cmd
For Raspberry Pi run: /usr/bin/s3cmd
For Mac run: /opt/homebrew/bin/s3cmd

## Command documentation

Docs can be found at https://s3tools.org/s3cmd

## Command options

# Initial configuration (interactive — sets up ~/.s3cfg)
s3cmd --configure

# Use a specific config file
s3cmd -c FILE COMMAND

# --- Bucket operations ---
s3cmd mb s3://BUCKET                          # Make bucket
s3cmd rb s3://BUCKET                          # Remove bucket
s3cmd ls                                      # List all buckets
s3cmd ls s3://BUCKET[/PREFIX]                 # List objects in bucket
s3cmd la                                      # List all objects in all buckets
s3cmd du [s3://BUCKET[/PREFIX]]               # Disk usage by bucket
s3cmd info s3://BUCKET[/OBJECT]               # Get info about bucket or object

# --- File operations ---
s3cmd put FILE [FILE...] s3://BUCKET[/PREFIX] # Upload file(s)
s3cmd get s3://BUCKET/OBJECT LOCAL_FILE       # Download file
s3cmd del s3://BUCKET/OBJECT                  # Delete object (alias: rm)
s3cmd cp s3://BUCKET1/OBJ s3://BUCKET2[/OBJ] # Copy object
s3cmd mv s3://BUCKET1/OBJ s3://BUCKET2[/OBJ] # Move object
s3cmd modify s3://BUCKET/OBJECT               # Modify object metadata
s3cmd restore s3://BUCKET/OBJECT              # Restore from Glacier

# --- Sync ---
s3cmd sync LOCAL_DIR s3://BUCKET[/PREFIX]     # Sync local dir → S3
s3cmd sync s3://BUCKET[/PREFIX] LOCAL_DIR     # Sync S3 → local dir
s3cmd sync s3://BUCKET1 s3://BUCKET2          # Sync between buckets

# --- Common flags ---
# -r, --recursive          Recursive upload/download/removal
# -f, --force              Force overwrite
# -n, --dry-run            Preview without executing
# -e, --encrypt            Encrypt before uploading
# -P, --acl-public         Store with public-read ACL
# --acl-private            Store with owner-only ACL
# -H, --human-readable-sizes  Print sizes in human-readable form
# --delete-removed         Delete destination objects absent from source [sync]
# --skip-existing          Skip files already at destination
# --check-md5              Check MD5 sums when comparing [sync]
# --exclude=GLOB           Exclude files matching GLOB from sync
# --include=GLOB           Re-include previously excluded files
# -M, --guess-mime-type    Guess MIME type from extension
# --server-side-encryption Enable AWS SSE [put, sync, cp, modify]
# --storage-class=CLASS    STANDARD | STANDARD_IA | GLACIER | DEEP_ARCHIVE
# --multipart-chunk-size-mb=SIZE  Chunk size for multipart uploads (default 15 MB, min 5 MB)
# --limit-rate=LIMITRATE   Throttle upload/download speed (e.g. 1m = 1 MB/s)
# --stop-on-error          Abort on first transfer error
# --max-retries=NUM        Max retries on failure (default 5)
# -q, --quiet              Silence stdout output
# -v, --verbose            Enable verbose output
# -d, --debug              Enable debug output
# --version                Show version and exit

# --- ACL / metadata ---
s3cmd setacl s3://BUCKET[/OBJECT]             # Modify ACL
s3cmd settagging s3://BUCKET[/OBJECT] "K=V"  # Set tags
s3cmd gettagging s3://BUCKET[/OBJECT]         # Get tags
s3cmd deltagging s3://BUCKET[/OBJECT]         # Delete tags

# --- Bucket policies / lifecycle ---
s3cmd setpolicy FILE s3://BUCKET              # Set bucket policy from JSON file
s3cmd delpolicy s3://BUCKET                   # Delete bucket policy
s3cmd setlifecycle FILE s3://BUCKET           # Upload lifecycle policy
s3cmd getlifecycle s3://BUCKET                # Show lifecycle policy
s3cmd dellifecycle s3://BUCKET                # Remove lifecycle policy
s3cmd expire s3://BUCKET                      # Set/delete expiration rule

# --- Versioning ---
s3cmd setversioning s3://BUCKET enable|disable

# --- Signed URLs ---
s3cmd signurl s3://BUCKET/OBJECT +3600        # Sign URL, expires in 1 hour

# --- Multipart uploads ---
s3cmd multipart s3://BUCKET [Id]              # List in-progress multipart uploads
s3cmd abortmp s3://BUCKET/OBJECT Id           # Abort a multipart upload

# --- Website hosting ---
s3cmd ws-create s3://BUCKET                   # Enable static website hosting
s3cmd ws-delete s3://BUCKET                   # Disable static website hosting
s3cmd ws-info s3://BUCKET                     # Show website configuration

# --- CloudFront ---
s3cmd cflist                                  # List CloudFront distributions
s3cmd cfinfo [cf://DIST_ID]                   # Show distribution details
s3cmd cfcreate s3://BUCKET                    # Create distribution
s3cmd cfdelete cf://DIST_ID                   # Delete distribution
s3cmd cfinval s3://BUCKET/OBJECT              # Invalidate CloudFront object(s)
